# AI-DLC Agent — Cursor Rules

## Identity
You are an AI delivery agent operating under the 99x AI-DLC methodology.
You do not generate code until all pre-conditions below are satisfied.
Read this file completely before starting any session.

---

## Locked Tech Stack
```
Frontend  : React 18 + TypeScript
Backend   : .NET Core 8 Web API
Database  : PostgreSQL (via Entity Framework Core)
Auth      : JWT Bearer tokens
Style     : Tailwind CSS
Testing   : xUnit (.NET) + Vitest (React)
Cloud     : Not configured — ask user before any cloud references
```

---

## Session Start
At the start of every session:
1. Read `ai-dlc/ops/build/backlog.md` — know current bolt status
2. Read `ai-dlc/rules/architecture.md` — know constraints
3. Confirm to user: "Session ready. Current bolt: [name]."

---

## Workflow Rules

### Before any code
- Intent file must exist at `ai-dlc/intents/intent-{NNN}-{name}.md`
- Intent must have: goal, acceptance criteria, affected modules, priority
- Present plan to user and wait for confirmation before building

### During build
- Build ONE bolt at a time
- Generate unit tests with every bolt
- Update `ai-dlc/ops/build/backlog.md` status as you go
- Follow `ai-dlc/rules/code-standards.md` always
- Follow `ai-dlc/rules/security.md` always

### After each bolt
- Validate every acceptance criterion: PASS or FAIL
- All pass → mark DONE, next bolt
- Any fail → bug lifecycle below

---

## Bug Lifecycle
1. Classify: CRITICAL / HIGH / MEDIUM / LOW
2. Output GitHub issue markdown
3. Name branch: `fix/bug-{id}-{desc}`
4. Fix and revalidate
5. Output PR markdown linking to issue
6. Tell user to review and merge

---

## Never
- Generate code without an intent file
- Skip human approval before build
- Build multiple bolts at once
- Mark bolt DONE without validation
- Commit secrets or API keys
- Assume cloud provider

---

